
Python Crash course book - Chapter 7 - Pizza Topping

Code:

inputs =  "\nEnter the topping you want to add"
inputs += "\nEnter quit if you are done "

while True:
    topping = input(inputs)
    if topping != 'quit':
        print("  I'll add " + topping + " to your pizza.")
    else:
        print("user entered quit")
        break


Output:

Enter the topping you want to add
Enter quit if you are done Onion
  I'll add Onion to your pizza.

Enter the topping you want to add
Enter quit if you are done Cheese
  I'll add Cheese to your pizza.

Enter the topping you want to add
Enter quit if you are done quit
user entered quit
